{#
left.jinja
This template is used to generate a left slide-out navigation vertical bar for content pages.  
The navigation section should provide:
- a click-able logo in the upper-left of that section, that returns to the index.html page 
- the title of the site and page, under the logo 

This navigation template can be used to overlay the main content with navigation options, 
when activated (slid-out) by the user.
The navigation pages available can be found in the config file: /index.yaml, in the "site" 
section:  

```yaml
    nav_pages: ['about','people','pets','blogs']  # sets order / list of main pages for navs.  If missing or null, use all pages, in alpha order
```

If missing or null, use all pages found in the project root directory, except for index.html,
placed in alphabetical order, with label for the nav link being the filename (minus extension) in all caps.  
For example,  ABOUT  |  BLOGS  |  PEOPLE  |  PETS

Besides the /index.yaml in section site.nav_pages, there are no other configurations.  Like all pages, 
it should use the selected css and javascript files to ensure all activities are local-browser only, but
have an interactive feeling. 

#}
<aside class="left-nav" id="leftNav">
    <button class="left-nav-handle" onclick="toggleLeftNav()" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <img src="/src/icons/hamburger.svg" alt="Menu" class="hamburger-icon">
    </button>
    <div class="left-nav-content">
        <div class="nav-header">
            <a href="/index.html" class="nav-brand">
                <img src="/src/images/{{ site.logo | default('logo.png') }}" alt="{{ site.title }}" class="nav-logo">
                <div class="nav-titles">
                    <h3 class="site-title">{{ site.title }}</h3>
                    <h4 class="page-title">{{ page.title }}</h4>
                </div>
            </a>
            <button class="nav-close" onclick="closeLeftNav()" aria-label="Close navigation">&times;</button>
        </div>
        
        <nav class="nav-menu">
            <ul class="nav-links">
                {% if site and site.nav_pages %}
                    {% for page_name in site.nav_pages %}
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a href="/{{ page_name }}.html" class="nav-link">{{ page_name.upper() }}</a>
                    </li>
                    {% endfor %}
                {% else %}
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a href="/about.html" class="nav-link">ABOUT</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a href="/people.html" class="nav-link">PEOPLE</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a href="/pets.html" class="nav-link">PETS</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a href="/blogs.html" class="nav-link">BLOGS</a>
                    </li>
                {% endif %}
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </div>
    <div class="nav-overlay" onclick="closeLeftNav()"></div>
</aside>